value.0: You're not supposed to be in here. Leave now and I may let you live.
How in the name of the gods did you get in here?! Prepare to be destroyed... UTTERLY!!
Wait... you must be <FirstName>. You took so long I assumed you didn't make it past the first floor, or abandoned the task like so many of your fickle common folk.
Well then, "recruit". I presume that you are looking for work? Or is this about some sort of cure for the Wailing Death?
Not so fast. You see, the authorities in Neverwinter promised me a lackey that will do my bidding. And you haven't done a single thing for me yet.
You're getting how this works. Keep that in mind and we'll get along nicely.

The job I have for you is quite simple: retrieve my "Spellbook of Inescapable Mazes". It was stolen by one of my rogue apprentices. I think you can guess what happened next when she attempted to use it to escape.
I have a few spare scrolls I copied from the book, so I can teleport you there. Unfortunately for her, that spellbook does not function while inside the demiplane.
It has been a few weeks, so she is most likely dead. I've already activated the recall portal, so you can come back anytime. Are you ready to leave?
Fine. I suppose I'll be waiting here, then.
Prepare yourself.
You're back. Do you have the spellbook?
Hmph. You know, my spellbook isn't going to grow legs and run back to me.
Alright, in you go.
Blasted fool. She must have gotten desperate and kept using the book, thinking it would do something. Such a damned waste.
Oh well, there's nothing you could have done, really. I suppose now I'll have to tell you about the cure for the Wailing Death.
The truth is, I don't know what the cure is. I can, however, tell you who is spreading the Wailing Death. Interested?
Oh boohoo. You have failed to successfully retrieve my spellbook, so we both didn't get what we want. But because I'm such a nice person, I'll continue.
Let's just say our strict barrier and armed guards are there for a purpose. We aren't keeping just rabble out, but a specific organization.
Honestly, people can just come and go. The plague doesn't seem to spread from person to person. That's why you see our nobles still visiting the Moonstone Mask, for one.
It wasn't until one of our own was "blessed" by a visiting priest of Helm. Soon after, he started showing signs of the Wailing Death and soon succumbed to it.
Since then, people who are unknown to us are not allowed entry. They could be a priest of Helm in disguise.
Believe what you will. Why don't you get a "blessing" from them and see for yourself? As for their intentions, it's quite obvious that they want destroy Neverwinter. Beyond that is just guessing.
It's quite simple. What the Helmites are doing is trying to destroy the city. You, on the other hand, are saving it. Your goals do not align with one another.
I guess it's time for you to get back to your master. Stop by and visit if you are looking for work. I may have a job for someone as capable as you.
What do you want now?
Farewell indeed.
*sigh* I'm not even going to ask why.

I'm always in search of magical trinkets. I've actually detected some gems of power nearby, outside in the roads of Neverwinter. Apparently, they're carried by some mages that have turned to banditry.
Now, I don't know which ones have it, nor can I provide you a way to exit Neverwinter. I leave both of these problems for you to figure out. Just one gem will do, and I will reward you handsomely.
Fine. Your loss. Was there anything else? I don't care much for idle chatter.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> Why are you showing me this plain old rock? That's not it at all, idiot. Go and find me an actual gem of power, before I get even angrier.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Hmm... I suppose this will do. I can't detect anything magical about it, but perhaps it is warded. Very well, here is your reward. Off with you, now.
Then I shall await your return.
Excellent. This one is a fine specimen.. Here is your payment, as well as some potions I was going to get rid of. Now, off with you - I have experiments to tend to.
The cure, of course. Tell me what is needed to cure the plague!
I'm here for the cure. What do I need to do to get you to tell me?
Let me guess, she "mazed" herself. And you want me to enter the maze in order to retrieve it.
I'm not ready to go yet.
I'm ready. Send me in.
I must be going now.
I need to return to the maze.
The book has pretty much turned to dust. It's useless.
This isn't what we agreed upon!
That's better than nothing. Go on.
I don't believe it. Why would the Helmites do this?
How can you tell that I'm not one?
Thanks for the info. I better get going.
Nothing. Farewell.
I would like to enter the maze.
You were saying something about someone spreading the Wailing Death?
Did you have any work for me?
I'm not interested.
<StartCheck>[Bluff]</Start> I believe this is the gem you are looking for.
I'll get one of those gems for you.
I have a gem of power for you.
Farewell.
